cond             Scilab Group             Scilab Function              cond
NAME
   cond - condition number
  
CALLING SEQUENCE
 cond(X)
PARAMETERS
 X    : real or complex square matrix
      
DESCRIPTION
   Condition number in 2-norm.  cond(X) is the  ratio  of  the largest
  singular value of  X  to the smallest.
  
EXAMPLE
 A=testmatrix('hilb',6);
 cond(A)
SEE ALSO
   rcond, svd  
  
